			<h1>1. India has achieved 75% of the 'Green Building Footprint'<br>&ensp;&ensp;target in 2020</h1>
 
			<p><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;India has successfully achieved 7.17 billion square feet of 'Green Building Footprint',<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;according to the recent data by the Indian Green Building Council.</p>
 
			<p class="p1"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;India has successfully achieved 7.17 billion square feet of 'Green Building Footprint'</p>
  
			<p class="p2"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;IGBC has set the target of 10 billion square feet of green buildings by 2022</p>
  
			<p class="p3"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;Maharashtra tops the list of green building leaders, followed by Karnataka, Haryana,<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;Tamil Nadu & UP</p>

			<p class="p4"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;As of date, there are almost 6,000 green projects and over 5.77 lakh acres<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;of large development projects in the country, which have helped to achieve the 75%<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;of the green building footprint target, two years earlier than the actual target.</p>

		</div>

