			<h1> 2. Green building Rating System</h1>
 
			<p><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;According to the IGBC, there are different categories and standards to be classified as a<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;green building, but all of them must have at least one of the following features -</p>

			<p class="p1"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;1. Conform to all environmental & building laws</p>

			<p class="p2"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;2. Share energy and water usage for 5 years from inception</p>

			<p class="p3"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;3. Minimise impact on the environment</p>

			<p class="p4"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;4. Use at least 30% less water and energy than others</p>

			<p class="p5"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;The Indian Green Building Council has launched 26 holistic ratings catering to the<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;design, construction, and operation of almost all project typologies.</p>

			<p class="p6"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;IGBC is also a founding member of the World Green Building Council – the nodal body of<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;country councils from across the globe.

		</div>

		<div class="sec-4">
				
			<img class="main-img" src="Footprint3.jpg">
			<img class="icon" src="icon.png"/>
			<h1>3. Achievement</h1>
			
			<p><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;We have now achieved 75% of our dream to facilitate 10 billion square feet of<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;green building footprint by 2022.</p>
			
			<p class="p1"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;India can become a world leader in a sustainable built environment only with the<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;continued support, guidance & involvement of various national<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;and international stakeholders.</p>
			
			<p class="p2"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;All the IGBC rating systems are designed to address national priorities and <br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;are facilitating in meeting many of the sustainable development goals<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;developed by the United Nations.</p>

		</div>

		<div class="sec-5">
			
			<img class="main-img" src="Footprint4.jpg">
