			<h1>4. India ranks third globally when it comes to green buildings</h1>

			<p><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;According to the United States Green Building Council, India ranks third globally<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;when it comes to green buildings, only behind Mainland China and Canada,<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;and the number is steadily increasing.</p> 

			<p class="p1"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;Within India, Maharashtra tops the list of green building leaders, followed by<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;Karnataka, Haryana, Tamil Nadu & Uttar Pradesh, according to the LEED<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;(Leadership in Energy & Environmental Design) survey of GCB-India.</p>

			<p class="p2"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;Mahesh Ramanujam, President & CEO of USGBC & GCBI applauds India’s efforts to become<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp; environment-friendly and says, “India continues to be a global leader in green building.</p>

			<p class="p3"><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>&ensp;By pursuing LEED certification for buildings and spaces, India is not only contributing<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;to economic growth and development but actively raising the living standard for its residents<br>&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;by providing more resilient, healthier & efficient buildings and communities.</p>

